         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that certain classes of high order accurate Galerkin approximations for homogeneous second-order hyperbolic equations, known to possess optimal order rate of convergence in $L^2$, also possess optimal order rate of convergence in $L^\infty$. This is attainable with particular smoothness assumptions on the initial data. We establish sufficient conditions for optimal $L^\infty$-convergence of the approximations to the solution and also the approximation to its time derivative. This is done for both semidiscrete approximations and for single-step fully discrete approximations generated by rational functions.</p>
          </abstract>
